how to tame a puppy i took in a stray female puppy thats half pit bull and something else her mother was dying and that was when i found her now she is pottying so bad around the house and i never had to go thru so much trouble getting her to stop peeing around the house someone help me i don't want to just throw her away but i'm trying to find a home for her also she been throwing up some spagehetti worms which i have never seen before and i have not the money to get her to a vet what do i do check and see if your community has a low cost vet sevice often through the humane society or animal control call some vets and flat out ask if they will help or can refer you to someone see if you can beg or borrow a pet crate to keep her in to try to housebreak hate to say it you may need to turn her over to animal control as her health problems may be more than meets the eye stray animals are unfortunately often unhelathy but to be optimistic good luck and bless your kind soul Housebreaking Crate training Dog Socialization Dog training Poker jargon The Amazing Race Guinea pig Inflation Rabies Craps Garfield Yu-Gi-Oh! anime, manga or movie only characters Rugrats Fancy rat Docking Dairy Pet skunk Blood (computer game) Sin City Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Veterinarian Futurama (TV series - season 2) Main characters of Fullmetal Alchemist Pitaten Sick Puppy Animal euthanasia Yu-Gi-Oh! anime and manga characters Kodocha Joseph (Hebrew Bible) Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an YuYu Hakusho Disgaea: Hour of Darkness Toilet humour Inuit mythology Puppy mill Timeline of alternative rock Animal shelter Avenue Q Pittsburgh Steelers The Life and Times of Juniper Lee Creatures in Bionicle Spidey Super Stories House Mouse One Tree Hill (TV series) Gliding Feral cat American Pit Bull Terrier American Civil Rights Movement (1955-1968) Worms weapons and tools Bull Terrier Ferret Domestication Social rule Baylisascaris Bat Boy Punk ideology Animal communication Nicomachean Ethics